498
00:20:11,011 --> 00:20:13,579
Oh, I see.

499
00:20:13,581 --> 00:20:17,382
He didn't have to
because you did it for him.

500
00:20:17,384 --> 00:20:19,651
That's not true.

501
00:20:19,653 --> 00:20:21,420
Then tell me what is true.

502
00:20:21,422 --> 00:20:24,256
Well, that's easy.

503
00:20:24,258 --> 00:20:26,425
You don't give a shit
about me or Harvey.

504
00:20:26,427 --> 00:20:28,260
This is a witch hunt,

505
00:20:28,262 --> 00:20:32,030
and I'm not gonna sit in
this room for another minute.

506
00:20:34,607 --> 00:20:35,707
I've worked with Harvey since

507
00:20:35,709 --> 00:20:37,368
he was a rookie
in the mail room.

508
00:20:37,413 --> 00:20:38,812
No way he buried that memo.

509
00:20:38,814 --> 00:20:40,814
You didn't see Donna
in that room.

510
00:20:40,816 --> 00:20:43,383
I'm not saying
she wouldn't do it if he asked.

511
00:20:43,385 --> 00:20:44,918
I'm saying he wouldn't ask.

512
00:20:44,920 --> 00:20:46,453
Wouldn't he?

513
00:20:46,455 --> 00:20:48,221
Because she's not
the only person I talked to.

514
00:20:48,414 --> 00:20:50,248
Now, a lot of people,
they don't like Harvey.

515
00:20:50,250 --> 00:20:51,949
But even the ones that love him

516
00:20:51,951 --> 00:20:55,653
say he likes to work
in the gray.

517
00:20:55,655 --> 00:20:57,255
I'd like Harvey
to sign this affidavit

518
00:20:57,257 --> 00:20:58,956
swearing that his office
never received the memo.

519
00:20:58,958 --> 00:20:59,957
Why?

520
00:20:59,959 --> 00:21:01,492
To put with
this motion to dismiss.

521
00:21:01,494 --> 00:21:04,328
If you wanted to file
a motion to dismiss,

522
00:21:04,330 --> 00:21:06,163
you would have
done that already.

523
00:21:06,165 --> 00:21:09,600
You want me to sign that thing
to cover your ass.

524
00:21:09,602 --> 00:21:11,335
Do I think it's likely

525
00:21:11,337 --> 00:21:12,937
that this case
is gonna get dismissed?

526
00:21:12,939 --> 00:21:16,841
No, but it's worth a shot,
and to your point,

527
00:21:16,843 --> 00:21:18,809
I'm not just doing this
to cover my ass.

528
00:21:18,811 --> 00:21:22,313
I'm doing it to cover your ass.

529
00:21:22,315 --> 00:21:25,383
File the motion.

530
00:21:25,385 --> 00:21:27,418
Harvey will sign
whatever I put in front of him.

531
00:21:33,225 --> 00:21:34,659
I give you one simple task.

532
00:21:34,661 --> 00:21:36,260
Bruno isn't eating,
so you give him milk.

533
00:21:36,262 --> 00:21:38,996
- I did.
- This is half-and-half.

534
00:21:38,998 --> 00:21:41,065
I thought he'd like it.
It's creamier.

535
00:21:41,067 --> 00:21:42,433
Hey, you know what,
maybe next time

536
00:21:42,435 --> 00:21:45,269
I'll just hand my cat over
to Michael Vick.

537
00:21:53,645 --> 00:21:55,846
Is that a cat carrier
in your hand?

538
00:21:55,848 --> 00:21:57,081
No.

539
00:21:57,083 --> 00:21:59,216
Is there a cat in that thing?

540
00:21:59,218 --> 00:22:00,518
It's called
a feline transportation unit.

541
00:22:00,520 --> 00:22:01,986
Cat carrier.

542
00:22:01,988 --> 00:22:02,987
Okay, they wouldn't call it
a cat carrier

543
00:22:02,989 --> 00:22:04,322
when it costs $400.

544
00:22:04,324 --> 00:22:06,157
- Do they call it a rip-off?
- Okay, you know what,

545
00:22:06,159 --> 00:22:08,192
I don't have time for this.
Besides, I'm late as it is.

546
00:22:08,194 --> 00:22:10,828
I have to ask.
What appointment?

547
00:22:10,830 --> 00:22:12,463
- Dentist.
- With a cat?

548
00:22:12,465 --> 00:22:14,231
- For the cat.
- You take him to a cat dentist?

549
00:22:14,233 --> 00:22:15,566
I can't take him to my dentist.

550
00:22:15,568 --> 00:22:17,301
Dr. Schneller wouldn't know
what to do with him.

551
00:22:17,303 --> 00:22:18,836
- Dr. Richard Schneller?
- Good-bye, Harvey.

552
00:22:18,838 --> 00:22:20,338
I don't want to hear it.

553
00:22:20,340 --> 00:22:21,572
If it's bad news,
I don't want to hear it.

554
00:22:21,574 --> 00:22:23,040
- You seem upset.
- Of course I'm upset.

555
00:22:23,042 --> 00:22:24,108
I just found out
that Louis and I

556
00:22:24,110 --> 00:22:25,376
share the same dentist.

557
00:22:25,378 --> 00:22:26,477
Have you spoken to Donna yet?

558
00:22:26,479 --> 00:22:27,545
No, and I'm pissed about it.

559
00:22:27,547 --> 00:22:28,879
I need her to get me
a new dentist.

560
00:22:28,881 --> 00:22:30,247
Well, we have a problem,

561
00:22:30,249 --> 00:22:31,082
whether you want
to hear it or not.

562
00:22:31,084 --> 00:22:32,450
What?

563
00:22:32,452 --> 00:22:33,984
Marco needs to be emancipated
from his father.

564
00:22:33,986 --> 00:22:35,219
But that's not a problem.
That's what we're doing.

565
00:22:35,221 --> 00:22:36,220
No, I don't mean
to let him play.

566
00:22:36,222 --> 00:22:38,456
I mean to keep him safe.

567
00:22:38,458 --> 00:22:40,424
That is directly
from the hospital.

568
00:22:40,426 --> 00:22:42,326
His dad did that to him.

569
00:22:42,328 --> 00:22:43,961
We need to get him away
from his father.

570
00:22:43,963 --> 00:22:45,296
I need to get him away.

571
00:22:45,298 --> 00:22:47,264
I set the hearing,
and I'm going to win.

572
00:22:47,266 --> 00:22:48,532
I'm hearing
a lot of "I" s in there.

573
00:22:48,534 --> 00:22:49,934
- Harvey...
- This isn't housing court.

574
00:22:49,936 --> 00:22:51,302
This is a kid's life.

575
00:22:51,304 --> 00:22:52,837
I know that,
and the only reason

576
00:22:52,839 --> 00:22:54,105
you know that
is because I gave a shit

577
00:22:54,107 --> 00:22:55,639
about this kid's life
in the first place.

578
00:22:55,641 --> 00:22:57,742
You think I didn't think
I was smarter

579
00:22:57,744 --> 00:22:59,543
than the guy
I started working for?

580
00:22:59,545 --> 00:23:02,947
I did, and I was,
and I waited my goddamn turn.

581
00:23:02,949 --> 00:23:04,749
Harvey, I'm ready.

582
00:23:04,751 --> 00:23:05,916
It's time to let me
out of the gate.

583
00:23:05,918 --> 00:23:07,852
Allison's filing
a motion to dismiss.

584
00:23:07,854 --> 00:23:10,488
She's swinging for the fences,
I'll give her that.

585
00:23:10,490 --> 00:23:12,656
You know what, I'm gonna
swing for the fences too.

586
00:23:12,658 --> 00:23:14,024
Mike's going to court.

587
00:23:14,026 --> 00:23:16,227
- I am?
- What's the case?

588
00:23:16,229 --> 00:23:17,762
Emancipation.

589
00:23:17,764 --> 00:23:19,764
- From him?
- I wish.

590
00:23:19,766 --> 00:23:21,031
He doesn't need
a court order for that.

591
00:23:21,033 --> 00:23:22,700
- Our little baby's growing up.
- Okay.

592
00:23:22,702 --> 00:23:24,535
Listen, I need you
to sign this affidavit

593
00:23:24,537 --> 00:23:26,704
that we never received
that memo from Coastal Motors.

594
00:23:49,361 --> 00:23:52,363
Oh, my God! Oh, I'm...

595
00:23:52,365 --> 00:23:54,799
There are napkins over there.

596
00:23:54,801 --> 00:23:57,368
I knew he wasn't a lawyer.
I didn't think he was an idiot.

597
00:23:57,370 --> 00:23:58,369
I knew he was an idiot.

598
00:23:58,371 --> 00:23:59,637
I didn't know he was spastic.

599
00:23:59,639 --> 00:24:01,305
I'm sorry, guys.

600
00:24:01,307 --> 00:24:02,673
When you get this cleaned up,
come see me.

601
00:24:02,675 --> 00:24:04,942
I'll get you a fresh one.

602
00:24:04,944 --> 00:24:07,011
- What the hell was that?
- What?

603
00:24:07,013 --> 00:24:08,646
- You know what.
- It was an accident.

604
00:24:08,648 --> 00:24:09,680
It was intentional.

605
00:24:09,682 --> 00:24:11,182
You ambushed me
with a cup of coffee.

606
00:24:11,184 --> 00:24:13,951
Think I haven't seen <i>Ronin?</i>

607
00:24:13,953 --> 00:24:15,085
It was all I could think of.

608
00:24:15,087 --> 00:24:16,153
Meaning?

609
00:24:16,155 --> 00:24:18,289
Donna was supposed to tell you.

610
00:24:18,291 --> 00:24:19,623
Tell me what?

611
00:24:19,625 --> 00:24:20,991
You can't sign the affidavit.

612
00:24:20,993 --> 00:24:25,229
You'll be committing perjury.

613
00:24:33,438 --> 00:24:35,606
What the hell
were you thinking?

614
00:24:35,608 --> 00:24:37,107
I didn't know how to tell you.

615
00:24:37,109 --> 00:24:39,243
"Harvey, I found the memo."
Is that so goddamn hard?

616
00:24:39,245 --> 00:24:42,246
You don't understand.
It had my name on it.

617
00:24:42,248 --> 00:24:44,682
I stamped it in.
That implicates you.

618
00:24:44,684 --> 00:24:46,183
Did you keep it
from me four years ago?

619
00:24:46,185 --> 00:24:48,519
I don't even remember
seeing it four years ago.

620
00:24:48,521 --> 00:24:50,020
Then I don't give a shit
what it implicates.

621
00:24:50,022 --> 00:24:51,522
You don't keep it from me now.

622
00:24:51,524 --> 00:24:53,357
I had never made
a mistake like that,

623
00:24:53,359 --> 00:24:54,825
and I thought
that I needed to...

624
00:24:54,827 --> 00:24:56,460
Look, keeping it from me
isn't a mistake.

625
00:24:56,462 --> 00:24:59,396
It's a decision.
I wanted to protect you.

626
00:24:59,398 --> 00:25:01,365
Lying to me doesn't protect me.

627
00:25:01,367 --> 00:25:03,467
It betrays me. Betrays you?

628
00:25:03,469 --> 00:25:05,202
If I had told you the truth...

629
00:25:05,204 --> 00:25:07,104
You don't keep things from me!

630
00:25:07,106 --> 00:25:08,138
You keep things from me
all the time!

631
00:25:08,140 --> 00:25:09,607
That's because I'm your boss.

632
00:25:09,609 --> 00:25:11,775
Well, maybe you shouldn't
be my boss anymore.

633
00:25:14,546 --> 00:25:16,280
I did what I thought
I had to do for you,

634
00:25:16,282 --> 00:25:19,483
and if you can't...

635
00:25:19,485 --> 00:25:21,118
just fire me.

636
00:25:21,120 --> 00:25:22,286
Let me explain
something to you.

637
00:25:22,288 --> 00:25:24,388
That memo doesn't hurt me.
It helps me.

638
00:25:24,390 --> 00:25:26,724
If I had buried it,
we wouldn't have it.

639
00:25:26,726 --> 00:25:30,227
But you found it,
so that's a good thing.

640
00:25:30,229 --> 00:25:31,996
What?

641
00:25:31,998 --> 00:25:34,832
Wh-what'd you do?

642
00:25:34,834 --> 00:25:36,667
Oh, what did you do?

643
00:25:36,669 --> 00:25:38,836
Allison
had that freaking camera,

644
00:25:38,838 --> 00:25:41,305
and I was...

645
00:25:41,307 --> 00:25:43,440
she implied that we were...

646
00:25:43,442 --> 00:25:45,943
What did you do?

647
00:25:45,945 --> 00:25:47,945
It's gone.

648
00:25:47,947 --> 00:25:51,215
You destroyed it?

649
00:25:52,751 --> 00:25:54,285
I'm not going
to fire you, Donna.

650
00:25:54,287 --> 00:25:58,322
I might kill you,
but I'm not gonna fire you.

651
00:25:58,324 --> 00:25:59,757
What are you going to do?

652
00:25:59,759 --> 00:26:02,526
What you should've done
from day one.

653
00:26:09,200 --> 00:26:10,501
Let me get this straight.

654
00:26:10,503 --> 00:26:12,136
Your own assistant
destroys evidence,

655
00:26:12,138 --> 00:26:13,170
and you still want
to go to trial?

656
00:26:13,172 --> 00:26:14,538
- Yes.
- No.

657
00:26:14,540 --> 00:26:16,273
You need to cut a deal
right now.

658
00:26:16,275 --> 00:26:18,375
You mean we need
to cut a deal, right,

659
00:26:18,377 --> 00:26:19,810
because we're
all on the same side?

660
00:26:19,812 --> 00:26:21,345
Harvey.

661
00:26:21,347 --> 00:26:22,313
You think I didn't know
what you were up to

662
00:26:22,315 --> 00:26:23,981
with that affidavit?

663
00:26:23,983 --> 00:26:25,449
I was advising my client,
the firm.

664
00:26:25,451 --> 00:26:28,319
You once told me
I was the firm.

665
00:26:28,321 --> 00:26:31,055
She came to me and thought
that you were in on it.

666
00:26:31,057 --> 00:26:32,923
I said no way.

667
00:26:32,925 --> 00:26:35,059
She wanted you
to sign that thing.

668
00:26:35,061 --> 00:26:37,361
I'm the leader of this firm.
I made a decision.

669
00:26:37,363 --> 00:26:40,331
You were happy to do it.
Don't blame me for Donna.

670
00:26:40,333 --> 00:26:43,901
I'm not, but I need to know
if you still believe me.

671
00:26:43,903 --> 00:26:45,903
- I do.
- That's beside the point.

672
00:26:45,905 --> 00:26:48,072
We have a decision to make.
There is no decision.

673
00:26:48,074 --> 00:26:50,240
We need to cut a deal... today.

674
00:26:50,242 --> 00:26:51,208
You know what,
that's the difference

675
00:26:51,210 --> 00:26:52,409
between us, Allison.

676
00:26:52,411 --> 00:26:54,445
You want to lose small.
I want to win big.

677
00:26:54,447 --> 00:26:56,914
She's the one
who has to try the case.

678
00:26:56,916 --> 00:26:58,048
Regardless of what Donna did,

679
00:26:58,050 --> 00:26:59,249
I never saw the memo.

680
00:26:59,251 --> 00:27:00,751
Are you gonna
sell a jury on that?

681
00:27:00,753 --> 00:27:03,420
Maybe the same way you sold it
to the Randall family.

682
00:27:03,422 --> 00:27:06,256
We have a window to settle this
before we have to disclose,

683
00:27:06,258 --> 00:27:07,658
but it's closing,
and when it does,

684
00:27:07,660 --> 00:27:09,226
we could offer them the moon.

685
00:27:09,228 --> 00:27:10,427
They're not gonna take it.
What's the downside of asking?

686
00:27:10,429 --> 00:27:12,062
We went through this
with the nurses.

687
00:27:12,064 --> 00:27:15,799
It tells them we're weak.
We are weak.

688
00:27:15,801 --> 00:27:18,636
Set it up.

689
00:27:18,638 --> 00:27:22,272
And whatever you're thinking,
I don't want to hear it.

690
00:27:56,060 --> 00:27:59,229
Mr. Mendoza, you've
asserted that, as a parent,

691
00:27:59,231 --> 00:28:01,231
you have certain rights.

692
00:28:01,233 --> 00:28:02,666
Do those include
the right to discipline Marco

693
00:28:02,668 --> 00:28:04,434
as you see fit?

694
00:28:04,436 --> 00:28:06,036
Every parent has that right.

695
00:28:06,038 --> 00:28:08,705
The right to teach
your child a lesson.

696
00:28:08,707 --> 00:28:10,273
- Yes.
- When he defies you.

697
00:28:10,275 --> 00:28:12,809
If need be.

698
00:28:12,811 --> 00:28:15,412
And if need be,
do you get angry?

699
00:28:15,414 --> 00:28:17,714
Do you fly off the handle?
Do you become abusive?

700
00:28:17,716 --> 00:28:19,316
No, I would never go that far.

701
00:28:19,318 --> 00:28:20,650
Mr. Mendoza,
would you agree that,

702
00:28:20,652 --> 00:28:22,219
along with those rights,

703
00:28:22,221 --> 00:28:24,688
you have certain
responsibilities as a parent?

704
00:28:24,690 --> 00:28:26,556
Of course.

705
00:28:26,558 --> 00:28:28,024
The responsibility
to keep your son healthy?

706
00:28:28,026 --> 00:28:30,527
Marco gets up every day
at 4:30 to train.

707
00:28:30,529 --> 00:28:32,028
I think that one's covered.

708
00:28:32,030 --> 00:28:34,097
The responsibility
to keep your son safe?

709
00:28:34,099 --> 00:28:35,966
That's the first job
of every parent.

710
00:28:35,968 --> 00:28:37,734
Hmm.

711
00:28:37,736 --> 00:28:40,203
Let's talk about
May 18th of last year.

712
00:28:40,205 --> 00:28:41,438
You took your son
to the hospital

713
00:28:41,440 --> 00:28:44,207
where he was treated
for severe dehydration.

714
00:28:44,209 --> 00:28:45,342
Rushed my son to keep him safe.

715
00:28:45,344 --> 00:28:46,877
What I'm interested in

716
00:28:46,879 --> 00:28:48,979
is how he got dehydrated
in the first place.

717
00:28:48,981 --> 00:28:50,680
He was running laps.

718
00:28:50,682 --> 00:28:51,848
Hadn't you had an argument

719
00:28:51,850 --> 00:28:53,383
about going pro
the night before?

720
00:28:53,385 --> 00:28:55,218
Yes.

721
00:28:55,220 --> 00:28:58,522
And you wanted to teach him
a lesson, as was your right.

722
00:28:58,524 --> 00:29:00,657
What?

723
00:29:00,659 --> 00:29:03,193
He questioned your authority,
didn't he?

724
00:29:03,195 --> 00:29:04,694
He's done it before, hasn't he?

725
00:29:04,696 --> 00:29:06,162
And you don't like that,
do you?

726
00:29:06,164 --> 00:29:07,831
- You are twisting this.
- You got angry,

727
00:29:07,833 --> 00:29:09,966
you flew off the handle,
and you became abusive.

728
00:29:09,968 --> 00:29:11,334
Objection, badgering.

729
00:29:11,336 --> 00:29:12,702
Easy, Mr. Ross.

730
00:29:12,704 --> 00:29:14,437
Marco has never called 911.

731
00:29:14,439 --> 00:29:16,840
He's never reported me
to social services.

732
00:29:16,842 --> 00:29:17,874
He's never complained
to anyone.

733
00:29:17,876 --> 00:29:19,309
They never do.

734
00:29:19,311 --> 00:29:21,411
You think I put my own son
in the hospital?

735
00:29:21,413 --> 00:29:23,146
Oh, I've read this report.
I know you did.

736
00:29:23,148 --> 00:29:24,414
And I know you will again.

737
00:29:24,416 --> 00:29:26,850
You are a lying
little piece of shit.

738
00:29:26,852 --> 00:29:29,219
- And there it is.
- Mr. Mendoza, that's enough.

739
00:29:32,356 --> 00:29:35,225
No further questions.

740
00:29:40,866 --> 00:29:43,033
Oh, what the hell?
You don't sneak up like that.

741
00:29:43,035 --> 00:29:45,936
I wasn't sneaking up.
I was just getting coffee.

742
00:29:45,938 --> 00:29:47,804
Yeah, well,
the paralegal needs coffee.

743
00:29:47,806 --> 00:29:49,973
I guess the junior partner
needs to get out of her way.

744
00:29:49,975 --> 00:29:51,675
You know what, Louis,
if you treated people here

745
00:29:51,677 --> 00:29:53,410
just a tenth as nicely
as you treat your cat,

746
00:29:53,412 --> 00:29:55,812
they might not feel about you
the way that you know they do.

747
00:29:55,814 --> 00:29:57,814
I'm sorry.

748
00:29:57,816 --> 00:29:59,416
Is everything okay?

749
00:29:59,418 --> 00:30:03,520
No, I just have, like,
a condition with my tear ducts.

750
00:30:03,522 --> 00:30:06,022
Oh, my God.

