765
00:30:54,873 --> 00:30:56,806
Not everything's about you,
you know.

766
00:30:56,808 --> 00:30:58,908
Now, you see,
that's where you're wrong.

767
00:31:00,144 --> 00:31:02,479
What's going on with Donna?

768
00:31:02,481 --> 00:31:03,780
I don't know.

769
00:31:03,782 --> 00:31:05,915
What do you mean?

770
00:31:05,917 --> 00:31:08,151
I saw you watching us
the other day.

771
00:31:08,153 --> 00:31:12,088
You know something.

772
00:31:12,090 --> 00:31:15,325
Come on, Mike, how many secrets
are you gonna keep from me?

773
00:31:15,327 --> 00:31:18,328
It's not mine. It's Donna's.

774
00:31:18,330 --> 00:31:19,996
I'm not saying you need
to give me specifics.

775
00:31:19,998 --> 00:31:23,767
I just need to know
that she's okay.

776
00:31:25,970 --> 00:31:29,939
She screwed up,
and it's not small.

777
00:31:29,941 --> 00:31:34,277
- What's gonna happen?
- Harvey's going to fix it.

778
00:31:34,279 --> 00:31:35,945
How do you know?

779
00:31:35,947 --> 00:31:38,615
You're gonna fix this
situation with Donna, right?

780
00:31:38,617 --> 00:31:41,084
- Why should I tell you?
- What?

781
00:31:41,086 --> 00:31:42,385
If I hadn't caught you,
when were you gonna tell me

782
00:31:42,387 --> 00:31:43,753
that she had that memo?

783
00:31:43,755 --> 00:31:45,188
I wasn't, 'cause
she promised me she would.

784
00:31:45,190 --> 00:31:46,856
Well, what would have
happened if you hadn't been

785
00:31:46,858 --> 00:31:49,092
in my office when Jessica
brought me that affidavit?

786
00:31:49,094 --> 00:31:50,293
That would've been
between you and Donna.

787
00:31:50,295 --> 00:31:52,996
And I would have
committed perjury.

788
00:31:52,998 --> 00:31:55,231
You're right.
I should have told you,

789
00:31:55,233 --> 00:31:58,134
or had Donna tell you then
and there, but I was thinking

790
00:31:58,136 --> 00:32:00,470
the fact that she actually
found this thing helps us.

791
00:32:00,472 --> 00:32:02,405
Yeah, it would've helped us.

792
00:32:02,407 --> 00:32:05,075
She destroyed it.

793
00:32:05,077 --> 00:32:06,876
- Whoa.
- Yeah.

794
00:32:06,878 --> 00:32:08,244
Whoa.

795
00:32:08,246 --> 00:32:09,646
Harvey, she was
backed into a corner.

796
00:32:09,648 --> 00:32:10,980
She made a bad call.

797
00:32:10,982 --> 00:32:12,449
Look, we can still...
Tell the truth?

798
00:32:12,451 --> 00:32:14,451
How do you think
that's going to play in court?

799
00:32:18,055 --> 00:32:20,390
Oh, my God. Um, I have to go.

800
00:32:20,392 --> 00:32:21,658
You screwed up with Marco,
didn't you?

801
00:32:21,660 --> 00:32:22,992
I'm on it.

802
00:32:22,994 --> 00:32:24,994
And this thing with Donna,
just let it go.

803
00:32:24,996 --> 00:32:28,431
I'm sure she said she was sorry.
She is sorry.

804
00:32:28,433 --> 00:32:31,634
But she never said it.

805
00:32:34,772 --> 00:32:36,706
Didn't expect to see you today.

806
00:32:36,708 --> 00:32:38,575
I wanted to get you the offer
as soon as I could.

807
00:32:38,577 --> 00:32:39,876
You could have called.

808
00:32:39,878 --> 00:32:42,312
No, I couldn't.

809
00:32:42,314 --> 00:32:44,147
Tanner's terms.

810
00:32:44,149 --> 00:32:45,582
The firm pays
$5 million in damages,

811
00:32:45,584 --> 00:32:46,750
as well as all legal fees.

812
00:32:46,752 --> 00:32:49,352
What else?

813
00:32:49,354 --> 00:32:51,454
Pearson Hardman
immediately and irrevocably

814
00:32:51,456 --> 00:32:55,892
strips Harvey Specter
of his senior partnership

815
00:32:55,894 --> 00:32:59,062
and reports him to
the New York Bar Association.

816
00:32:59,064 --> 00:33:01,164
I know this isn't
what you want to hear,

817
00:33:01,166 --> 00:33:05,335
but I would
take this deal and run.

818
00:33:11,542 --> 00:33:14,577
What do you want now?

819
00:33:14,579 --> 00:33:17,213
Sell me a vacuum cleaner?
Set of steak knives?

820
00:33:17,215 --> 00:33:18,348
I don't want
to sell you anything.

821
00:33:18,350 --> 00:33:20,150
I'm not here to do that.

822
00:33:20,152 --> 00:33:22,385
I'm here to tell you
that I'm sorry.

823
00:33:22,387 --> 00:33:26,055
I should have known
about that memo.

824
00:33:26,057 --> 00:33:27,624
But I didn't do my job.

825
00:33:27,626 --> 00:33:29,492
If I had, you and I
wouldn't be here right now.

826
00:33:29,494 --> 00:33:30,493
But we are here right now

827
00:33:30,495 --> 00:33:33,163
because of what you did
to my husband.

828
00:33:33,165 --> 00:33:35,799
I'm sorry. I'm so sorry.

829
00:33:35,801 --> 00:33:37,400
I never should have done it.

830
00:33:37,402 --> 00:33:41,504
My mother marched, Mr. lawyer.

831
00:33:41,506 --> 00:33:44,707
They set dogs on her.
I saw the scars.

832
00:33:44,709 --> 00:33:47,343
She said it wasn't the dogs,
it was the men.

833
00:33:47,345 --> 00:33:50,513
I say, put those dogs down.

834
00:33:52,748 --> 00:33:54,282
So you think
we should take this deal?

835
00:33:55,128 --> 00:33:57,095
I think we have to.

836
00:33:57,097 --> 00:33:58,763
Just say it.

837
00:33:58,765 --> 00:34:00,832
You want me
to cut Harvey loose.

838
00:34:00,834 --> 00:34:02,700
You've never been afraid
to spill blood before.

839
00:34:02,702 --> 00:34:04,502
You means yours.

840
00:34:04,504 --> 00:34:06,037
I was actually referring
to when you and I

841
00:34:06,039 --> 00:34:07,872
crossed the other names
off the letterhead.

842
00:34:07,874 --> 00:34:09,607
That was for
the good of the firm.

843
00:34:09,609 --> 00:34:11,743
Was it?

844
00:34:14,613 --> 00:34:16,381
Evidence was destroyed,
Jessica.

845
00:34:16,383 --> 00:34:19,884
- Not by Harvey.
- On his watch, therefore...

846
00:34:19,886 --> 00:34:20,919
On mine.

847
00:34:20,921 --> 00:34:22,353
If this were anyone else,

848
00:34:22,355 --> 00:34:23,621
you'd be seeing it
the same way I do.

849
00:34:23,623 --> 00:34:25,790
I'm not scapegoating him.

850
00:34:25,792 --> 00:34:28,259
You care about Harvey.
I know that.

851
00:34:28,261 --> 00:34:29,427
But I also know
that you care about

852
00:34:29,429 --> 00:34:31,529
your position in this firm.

853
00:34:31,531 --> 00:34:33,231
A law was broken.

854
00:34:33,233 --> 00:34:35,533
Are you really going
to sit by and do nothing?

855
00:34:39,839 --> 00:34:41,739
I've got to call you back.

856
00:34:41,741 --> 00:34:44,142
Did you get it?
Got it right here,

857
00:34:44,144 --> 00:34:45,977
fully executed emancipation.

858
00:34:45,979 --> 00:34:47,245
You tell Marco yet?

859
00:34:47,247 --> 00:34:48,046
No, I wanted you
to see it first.

860
00:34:48,048 --> 00:34:49,347
Nice job.

861
00:34:49,349 --> 00:34:50,548
This way I can call him
with the good news.

862
00:34:50,550 --> 00:34:53,518
- Yeah, just one problem.
- What's that?

863
00:34:53,520 --> 00:34:55,386
Marco lied.

864
00:34:55,388 --> 00:34:57,121
- What?
- Yeah.

865
00:34:57,123 --> 00:34:58,623
We got backed into a corner,

866
00:34:58,625 --> 00:35:00,191
and he knew the truth
wouldn't play in court,

867
00:35:00,193 --> 00:35:02,560
so he made up a story.

868
00:35:02,562 --> 00:35:04,929
If it was a lie, Michael,
then why didn't Oscar say so?

869
00:35:04,931 --> 00:35:06,397
Marco perjured himself.

870
00:35:06,399 --> 00:35:07,699
You really think his father

871
00:35:07,701 --> 00:35:09,100
was going to be the one
to point that out?

872
00:35:09,102 --> 00:35:10,802
- That's a lot of conjecture.
- Yeah, it would be.

873
00:35:10,804 --> 00:35:12,804
But I went to see Oscar.

874
00:35:12,806 --> 00:35:15,406
Turns out he wasn't even there
when Marco ran those laps.

875
00:35:15,408 --> 00:35:17,342
But you were.
Nuhuh, it's bullshit.

876
00:35:17,344 --> 00:35:19,410
I saw the look
on your face in court.

877
00:35:19,412 --> 00:35:21,880
You knew, and you did nothing.

878
00:35:24,717 --> 00:35:27,218
You got me.

879
00:35:27,220 --> 00:35:28,686
But it doesn't matter,
'cause we won.

880
00:35:28,688 --> 00:35:30,121
No, we didn't.

881
00:35:30,123 --> 00:35:32,857
'Cause I'm not filing papers
based on a lie.

882
00:35:32,859 --> 00:35:34,259
Harvey is gonna make you
regret that.

883
00:35:34,261 --> 00:35:37,428
Harvey's not gonna do shit.

884
00:35:37,430 --> 00:35:41,032
This is my case,
and you are done.

885
00:35:50,543 --> 00:35:52,143
♪

886
00:35:56,049 --> 00:35:58,016
We need to talk.

887
00:35:58,018 --> 00:36:00,018
It's subtle, but Daniel's
strong-arming me.

888
00:36:00,020 --> 00:36:01,019
Not now.

889
00:36:01,021 --> 00:36:03,221
My dad.

890
00:36:03,223 --> 00:36:04,823
♪

891
00:36:18,003 --> 00:36:19,404
I was wrong.

892
00:36:19,406 --> 00:36:22,006
Am I in the right office?

893
00:36:22,008 --> 00:36:24,442
I went to the plaintiffs again.

894
00:36:24,444 --> 00:36:26,511
Why?

895
00:36:26,513 --> 00:36:27,979
To tell them I was sorry.

896
00:36:27,981 --> 00:36:30,915
Harvey, there is
a deal on the table.

897
00:36:30,917 --> 00:36:33,685
Allison's right.

898
00:36:33,687 --> 00:36:36,054
I shouldn't be the lawyer.

899
00:36:36,056 --> 00:36:38,589
I don't even
make a good client.

900
00:36:38,591 --> 00:36:41,726
Neither do I.

901
00:36:41,728 --> 00:36:44,929
But I've got some hard news
I have to tell you.

902
00:36:47,866 --> 00:36:49,367
Okay, let me guess,

903
00:36:49,369 --> 00:36:50,802
you're here
to take me up on my offer

904
00:36:50,804 --> 00:36:52,737
to trade offices. No.

905
00:36:52,739 --> 00:36:55,807
But I did happen to find these.

906
00:36:55,809 --> 00:36:57,041
Who still eats Twinkies?

907
00:36:57,043 --> 00:36:59,844
Who doesn't still eat Twinkies?

908
00:36:59,846 --> 00:37:02,480
What's up?

909
00:37:02,482 --> 00:37:05,016
- I need a favor.
- Okay, what?

910
00:37:05,018 --> 00:37:07,285
Is this from
your tennis client?

911
00:37:07,287 --> 00:37:09,220
First one.

912
00:37:09,222 --> 00:37:10,989
Not as big as Harvey's.

913
00:37:10,991 --> 00:37:12,490
Really? You're gonna go there?

914
00:37:12,492 --> 00:37:14,625
It's probably gonna be
worth a lot of money someday.

915
00:37:14,627 --> 00:37:16,361
- Probably.
- I need it.

916
00:37:16,363 --> 00:37:17,729
It's important.

917
00:37:17,731 --> 00:37:20,498
What for?

918
00:37:20,500 --> 00:37:23,534
Why don't we
just call that my secret?

919
00:37:30,543 --> 00:37:32,010
Daniel,

920
00:37:32,012 --> 00:37:35,847
will you come to
my office right now please?

921
00:37:42,488 --> 00:37:43,855
Have a seat.

922
00:37:43,857 --> 00:37:46,290
Couldn't we have done this
in my office?

923
00:37:46,292 --> 00:37:49,494
Yes, we could have,
but I prefer to do it here...

924
00:37:49,496 --> 00:37:52,563
in your old office.

925
00:37:54,733 --> 00:37:56,200
What's this?

926
00:37:56,202 --> 00:37:58,336
I want you to
let Allison Holt go.

927
00:37:58,338 --> 00:38:00,538
- Why would I do that?
- Why you?

928
00:38:00,540 --> 00:38:02,673
Because you brought her in
initially.

929
00:38:02,675 --> 00:38:05,710
I am extending you
the courtesy of letting her go.

930
00:38:05,712 --> 00:38:08,246
As for why at all,

931
00:38:08,248 --> 00:38:11,516
I do care about
my position in this firm

932
00:38:11,518 --> 00:38:14,385
and my position is that we win.

933
00:38:14,387 --> 00:38:17,221
We win, Harvey wins,

934
00:38:17,223 --> 00:38:18,222
and I win.

935
00:38:18,224 --> 00:38:19,791
Allison Holt can't win,

936
00:38:19,793 --> 00:38:21,392
because she doesn't
believe in Harvey.

937
00:38:21,394 --> 00:38:24,295
I can, because I do.

938
00:38:24,297 --> 00:38:26,397
- It's your decision.
- It is.

939
00:38:26,399 --> 00:38:29,700
But don't try to pass it off
as a courtesy.

940
00:38:29,702 --> 00:38:31,969
You're trying to humiliate me,

941
00:38:31,971 --> 00:38:34,205
like you did by summoning me
into your office.

942
00:38:34,207 --> 00:38:37,375
I summoned you because
I wanted you to understand

943
00:38:37,377 --> 00:38:39,277
who you were
threatening earlier.

944
00:38:39,279 --> 00:38:41,879
I wasn't threatening you.

945
00:38:41,881 --> 00:38:44,415
I was pointing out facts. Yes.

946
00:38:44,417 --> 00:38:46,250
The fact that,
if I'm not careful,

947
00:38:46,252 --> 00:38:47,852
you'll try to take
this office back.

948
00:38:47,854 --> 00:38:49,821
That's not going to happen.

949
00:38:49,823 --> 00:38:55,193
And as for your point
about a law being broken,

950
00:38:55,195 --> 00:38:57,095
you're right.

951
00:38:57,097 --> 00:39:00,331
I'm not going to sit by
and do nothing.

952
00:39:01,834 --> 00:39:04,802
Louis, can I come in?

953
00:39:04,804 --> 00:39:09,373
I'm a little busy right now.

954
00:39:11,009 --> 00:39:13,744
Where'd you get this?

955
00:39:13,746 --> 00:39:17,548
I just know what
a huge tennis fan you are.

956
00:39:24,123 --> 00:39:26,891
Rachel...

957
00:39:30,095 --> 00:39:33,131
could you just close
the door on your way out?

958
00:39:33,133 --> 00:39:36,167
Sure thing, Louis.

959
00:39:56,388 --> 00:39:58,890
Harvey's not here.
He should be back soon.

960
00:39:58,892 --> 00:40:00,658
I'm not here to see Harvey.

961
00:40:00,660 --> 00:40:03,194
Oh.

962
00:40:03,196 --> 00:40:07,165
He wanted to be the one to
have this conversation with you.

963
00:40:07,167 --> 00:40:08,599
But it's my firm,

964
00:40:08,601 --> 00:40:11,402
and I wanted you
to hear it from me.

965
00:40:11,404 --> 00:40:13,104
Am I being fired?

966
00:40:13,106 --> 00:40:16,174
Yes.

967
00:40:16,176 --> 00:40:18,176
I appreciate everything
that you've done

968
00:40:18,178 --> 00:40:19,911
for Harvey and for me,

969
00:40:19,913 --> 00:40:23,147
but whatever
my personal feelings,

970
00:40:23,149 --> 00:40:26,250
your actions
have left me no choice

971
00:40:26,252 --> 00:40:28,486
but to terminate your employment
at Pearson Hardman

972
00:40:28,488 --> 00:40:30,888
effective immediately.

973
00:41:05,625 --> 00:41:07,225
♪

974
00:41:32,918 --> 00:41:35,886
You said
he was going to fix it.

975
00:41:37,923 --> 00:41:39,023
I thought he would.